WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.441 --> 00:00:05.318
Alright. lets see what
this thing can do.

2
00:00:05.485 --> 00:00:07.070
What's the SR-71's record?

3
00:00:07.278 --> 00:00:10.573
The altitude record for fixed-wing
flight is 85.000 feet. sir.

4
00:00:10.781 --> 00:00:13.117
Records are made
to be broken. C'mon!

5
00:00:16.620 --> 00:00:19.957
Sir. there is a potentially fatal
build-up of ice occurring.

6
00:00:20.123 --> 00:00:21.500
Keep going!

7
00:00:22.876 --> 00:00:24.336
Higher!

8
00:00:37.973 --> 00:00:40.350
We're iced up. Jarvis!
Deploy flaps.

9
00:00:41.059 --> 00:00:42.477
Jarvis?

10
00:00:44.396 --> 00:00:46.523
C'mon. we gotta break the ice!

11
00:01:20.512 --> 00:01:21.888
Cut power.

12
00:02:42.629 --> 00:02:45.924
Note: main transducer feels
sluggish at plus 40 altitude.

13
00:02:46.090 --> 00:02:48.009
The whole pressurization
is problematic.

14
00:02:48.217 --> 00:02:50.344
I'm thinking 'icy' is
a probable factor.

15
00:02:50.511 --> 00:02:53.305
A very astute observation. sir.
Perhaps if you intend to visit

16
00:02:53.472 --> 00:02:55.557
other planets. we should
improve the exo systems.

17
00:02:55.766 --> 00:02:58.185
Connect to the Cisco. have it
reconfigure the shell metals.

18
00:02:58.393 --> 00:03:01.104
Use the gold-titanium alloy from
the Seraphim tactical satellite.

19
00:03:01.313 --> 00:03:03.398
That should ensure
the fuselage integrity

20
00:03:03.607 --> 00:03:05.733
while maintaining power
-to-weight ratio. Got it?

21
00:03:05.900 --> 00:03:08.611
Yes. Shall I render using
proposed specifications?

22
00:03:08.820 --> 00:03:10.238
Thrill me.

23
00:03:11.364 --> 00:03:13.282
<i>Tonight's red hot.
red carpeted.</i>

24
00:03:13.282 --> 00:03:15.367
<i>right here at the
Disney Concert Hall.</i>

25
00:03:15.576 --> 00:03:18.245
<i>where Tony Stark's
third annual benefit for</i>

26
00:03:18.453 --> 00:03:21.331
<i>the Firefighters Family Fund
has become the place to be...</i>

27
00:03:21.581 --> 00:03:23.250
Jarvis. did we get
an invite from them?

28
00:03:23.416 --> 00:03:25.710
I have no record of
the invitation. sir.

29
00:03:26.127 --> 00:03:27.920
<i>...haven't been seen in public</i>

30
00:03:28.087 --> 00:03:30.923
<i>since his bizarre and highly
controversial press conference.</i>

31
00:03:31.132 --> 00:03:33.634
<i>Some claim he's suffering
from PTS and has been</i>

32
00:03:33.843 --> 00:03:36.428
<i>bed ridden for weeks.
Whatever the case may be.</i>

33
00:03:36.595 --> 00:03:39.473
<i>no one expects an appearance
from him tonight.</i>

34
00:03:39.890 --> 00:03:41.266
The render is complete.

35
00:03:41.766 --> 00:03:43.727
Little ostentatious.
don't you think?

36
00:03:43.935 --> 00:03:46.854
What was I thinking?
You're usually so discrete.

37
00:03:48.106 --> 00:03:50.900
Tell you what... throw a little
hot rot red in there.

38
00:03:51.067 --> 00:03:53.402
Yes. that shall help you
keep a low profile.

39
00:03:56.697 --> 00:03:58.615
The render is complete.

40
00:03:58.949 --> 00:04:00.867
Yeah. I like it.
Fabricate it and paint it.

41
00:04:01.034 --> 00:04:02.619
Commencing an
automated assembly.

42
00:04:02.827 --> 00:04:04.954
Estimated completion
time is five hours.

43
00:04:05.497 --> 00:04:07.457
Don't wait up for me. honey.

44
00:04:29.769 --> 00:04:31.479
The weapons manufacturing is...

45
00:04:31.687 --> 00:04:34.940
only a one small part of what
Stark Industries is all about...

46
00:04:39.820 --> 00:04:42.572
- Hey Tony. remember me?
- I sure don't.

47
00:04:43.531 --> 00:04:45.283
You look great. Hef.

48
00:04:47.994 --> 00:04:51.414
What's the world coming to when
a guy's gotta crash his own party?

49
00:04:51.914 --> 00:04:53.457
Look at you!

50
00:04:54.583 --> 00:04:57.169
- Hey. what a surprise!
- I'll see you inside.

51
00:04:59.129 --> 00:05:01.047
Listen. take it slow. alright?

52
00:05:01.214 --> 00:05:03.258
I got the Board where
I really want them.

53
00:05:03.466 --> 00:05:06.052
You got it. Just cabin fever.
I'll just be a minute.

54
00:05:10.598 --> 00:05:12.641
Give me a Scotch.
I'm starving.

55
00:05:13.601 --> 00:05:15.519
- Mr. Stark?
- Yeah?

56
00:05:15.769 --> 00:05:18.647
- Agent Coulson.
- Oh yeah. the guy from the...

57
00:05:18.897 --> 00:05:20.524
Strategic Homeland
Intervention

58
00:05:20.690 --> 00:05:22.609
Enforcement and
Logistics Division.

59
00:05:22.734 --> 00:05:24.569
God. you got... you need
a new name for that.

60
00:05:24.736 --> 00:05:26.279
Yeah. I hear that a lot.

61
00:05:26.696 --> 00:05:28.823
Listen. I know this must be
a trying time for you.

62
00:05:29.031 --> 00:05:30.533
but we need to debrief you.

63
00:05:30.741 --> 00:05:32.660
There's still a lot of
unanswered questions.

64
00:05:32.868 --> 00:05:34.578
and time can be a factor
with these things.

65
00:05:34.787 --> 00:05:36.497
Lets just put something
on the books.

66
00:05:36.705 --> 00:05:39.583
How about the 24th. at 7 p.m.
at Stark Industries?

67
00:05:40.250 --> 00:05:43.169
Tell you what... you got it.
You're absolutely right.

68
00:05:43.461 --> 00:05:47.507
Well... I'm gonna go to my
assistant and we'll make it date.

69
00:05:49.050 --> 00:05:50.968
You look fantastic.
I didn't recognise you.

70
00:05:51.177 --> 00:05:53.304
- What are you doing here?
- Avoiding government agents.

71
00:05:53.471 --> 00:05:55.806
- Are you here by yourself?
- Where'd you get that dress?

72
00:05:55.973 --> 00:05:58.141
It was a birthday present
from you. actually.

73
00:05:58.308 --> 00:06:00.227
- I have great taste.
- Yes.

74
00:06:00.394 --> 00:06:03.438
- You. uh. wanna dance?
- Oh. no. thank you. No.

75
00:06:14.698 --> 00:06:16.617
Am I making you uncomfortable?

76
00:06:16.992 --> 00:06:18.327
No. no.

77
00:06:18.911 --> 00:06:20.912
I always forget to
wear a deodorant.

78
00:06:21.121 --> 00:06:23.331
and dance with my boss
in front of everyone

79
00:06:23.540 --> 00:06:25.333
that I work with.
in a dress with no back.

80
00:06:26.125 --> 00:06:28.544
- You look great. you
smell great. - Oh. God.

81
00:06:28.711 --> 00:06:30.796
But I could fire you.
if that'd take the edge off.

82
00:06:30.963 --> 00:06:33.924
I actually don't think that you
could tie your shoes without me.

83
00:06:34.133 --> 00:06:35.467
- I'd make it a week.

84
00:06:35.676 --> 00:06:38.345
Really? What's your
social security number?

85
00:06:41.515 --> 00:06:43.099
- Five.
- Five?

86
00:06:44.642 --> 00:06:47.395
You're missing just a
couple of digits there.

87
00:06:47.604 --> 00:06:51.440
The other eight? That's why
I got you. for the other eight.

88
00:07:02.784 --> 00:07:05.703
- How about a little air?
- Yes. I need some air.

89
00:07:07.622 --> 00:07:09.582
- That was totally weird.
- Totally harmless.

90
00:07:09.791 --> 00:07:12.084
It was totally not harmless.
by the way.

91
00:07:12.251 --> 00:07:15.254
- Nobody was watching us.
- Everybody who I work with...

92
00:07:15.462 --> 00:07:18.298
I think you lost objectivity.
I think they... we just danced.

93
00:07:18.507 --> 00:07:20.258
No. it was not
just the dance!

94
00:07:20.467 --> 00:07:22.177
You don't understand
because you're you.

95
00:07:22.385 --> 00:07:25.472
And everybody knows exactly who
you are. and how you are with girls.

96
00:07:25.680 --> 00:07:27.849
And all that.
which is completely fine...

97
00:07:28.057 --> 00:07:31.102
But you know. then me. you're
my boss and I'm dancing...

98
00:07:31.310 --> 00:07:34.480
Because it makes me look like...
the one who's trying to...

99
00:07:34.647 --> 00:07:37.024
I just think you're
overstating. that's all.

100
00:07:37.232 --> 00:07:40.902
And we're here. and then I'm...
wearing this ridiculous dress...

101
00:07:41.194 --> 00:07:44.239
And then we were
dancing like that and...

102
00:07:56.709 --> 00:07:59.002
- I would like a drink. please.
- Got it.

103
00:08:00.962 --> 00:08:03.506
I would like a
vodka martini. please.

104
00:08:03.715 --> 00:08:06.301
Very dry with olives.
lot of olives.

105
00:08:06.509 --> 00:08:08.428
like at least three olives.

106
00:08:09.220 --> 00:08:12.139
Two vodka martinis. extra dry.
extra olives. extra fast.

107
00:08:12.348 --> 00:08:13.891
Make one of them dirty.

108
00:08:18.854 --> 00:08:22.065
- Well... Tony Stark!
- Oh. hey!

109
00:08:22.315 --> 00:08:24.025
Fancy seeing you here.

110
00:08:27.445 --> 00:08:29.322
- Carrie. - Christine.
- That's right.

111
00:08:29.614 --> 00:08:31.949
You have a lot of nerve
showing up here tonight.

112
00:08:32.241 --> 00:08:34.243
Can I at least get
a reaction from you?

113
00:08:34.451 --> 00:08:36.161
Panic. I would say
panic is my reaction.

114
00:08:36.370 --> 00:08:38.080
I was referring to your
company's involvement

115
00:08:38.288 --> 00:08:40.082
in this latest atrocity.
- They just put my name

116
00:08:40.248 --> 00:08:42.000
on the invitation.
I don't know what to tell you.

117
00:08:42.167 --> 00:08:43.960
I actually almost bought it.
hook. line and sinker.

118
00:08:44.169 --> 00:08:46.337
I was out of town for a couple
of months. in case you didn't hear.

119
00:08:46.546 --> 00:08:47.839
Is this what you call
accountability?

120
00:08:48.172 --> 00:08:51.092
It's a town called Gulmira.
Heard of it?

121
00:09:01.977 --> 00:09:04.646
- When were these taken?
- Yesterday.

122
00:09:04.854 --> 00:09:07.148
- I didn't approve any shipment.
- Well. your company did.

123
00:09:07.315 --> 00:09:09.067
Well. I'm not my company.

124
00:09:09.859 --> 00:09:12.528
- Please. do you mind?
- Have you seen these pictures?

125
00:09:12.903 --> 00:09:16.115
- What's going on? - Tony. you
can't afford to be this naive.

126
00:09:16.323 --> 00:09:18.242
I was naive before.
when they said:

127
00:09:18.450 --> 00:09:20.911
Here's the line. we don't cross it.
this is how we do business.

128
00:09:21.119 --> 00:09:24.122
If we're double-dealing
under the table... are we?

129
00:09:28.751 --> 00:09:30.711
Let's take a picture.
Come on.

130
00:09:31.087 --> 00:09:32.505
Picture time!

131
00:09:34.340 --> 00:09:37.009
Tony... who do you
think locked you out?

132
00:09:37.217 --> 00:09:40.345
I was the one who filed
the injunction against you.

133
00:09:42.514 --> 00:09:44.891
It's the only way
I can protect you.

134
00:09:56.652 --> 00:09:59.321
<i>The fifteen miles hike
to the outskirts of Gulmira</i>

135
00:09:59.529 --> 00:10:02.282
<i>can only be described
as a 'descent into Hell'.</i>

136
00:10:02.449 --> 00:10:04.576
<i>Into a modern day
heart of darkness.</i>

137
00:10:04.784 --> 00:10:07.245
<i>Simple farmers and herders
from peaceful villages</i>

138
00:10:07.453 --> 00:10:09.205
<i>have been driven
from their homes</i>

139
00:10:09.413 --> 00:10:11.332
<i>displaced from their
lands by warlords.</i>

140
00:10:11.540 --> 00:10:13.250
<i>emboldened by
a newfound power.</i>

141
00:10:13.542 --> 00:10:15.502
<i>Villagers have been
forced to take shelter</i>

142
00:10:15.669 --> 00:10:17.629
<i>in whatever ways
that they can find.</i>

143
00:10:17.838 --> 00:10:19.506
<i>In the ruins of other villages</i>

144
00:10:19.840 --> 00:10:22.759
<i>or here. in the remnants of
the old Soviet smelting plant.</i>

145
00:10:27.597 --> 00:10:30.099
<i>Recent violence has been
attributed to a group</i>

146
00:10:30.099 --> 00:10:33.519
<i>of foreign fighters. referred to
by locals as the Ten Rings.</i>

147
00:10:33.727 --> 00:10:36.814
<i>As you can see. these men are
heavily armed and on a mission.</i>

148
00:10:37.022 --> 00:10:40.650
<i>A mission that can prove fatal to
anyone who stands in their way.</i>

149
00:10:41.068 --> 00:10:43.778
<i>With no political will or
international pressure.</i>

150
00:10:43.778 --> 00:10:46.072
<i>there's very little hope
for these refugees.</i>

151
00:10:46.281 --> 00:10:49.158
<i>Around me. a woman begging
for news on her husband</i>

152
00:10:49.367 --> 00:10:51.285
<i>who was kidnapped
by insurgents.</i>

153
00:10:51.494 --> 00:10:52.995
<i>Either forced to
join their militia...</i>

154
00:10:58.083 --> 00:11:01.002
<i>...to anyone who will stop
a child's simple question:</i>

155
00:11:01.211 --> 00:11:03.588
<i>"Where are my
mother and father?"</i>

156
00:11:04.714 --> 00:11:07.091
<i>There's very little hope
for these refugees.</i>

157
00:11:07.258 --> 00:11:11.053
<i>refugees who can only wonder
who. if anyone. will help.</i>

158
00:12:40.010 --> 00:12:41.178
Faster!

159
00:12:41.386 --> 00:12:43.555
Women on the trucks!
The weapons here!

160
00:12:43.763 --> 00:12:45.849
Abandon houses!
Hurry up!

161
00:12:53.731 --> 00:12:55.399
Hold this rebel!

162
00:12:57.526 --> 00:12:59.653
Put him with the others.

163
00:13:04.866 --> 00:13:06.117
Father!

164
00:13:10.121 --> 00:13:11.664
What the hell is this?

165
00:13:22.507 --> 00:13:24.175
Kill this bastard!

166
00:13:24.592 --> 00:13:26.177
You are incompetent!

167
00:13:29.263 --> 00:13:30.723
Turn your head!

168
00:13:32.141 --> 00:13:33.726
Father!

169
00:14:34.240 --> 00:14:35.949
He is all yours.

170
00:15:30.374 --> 00:15:32.001
AIR BASE EDWARDS.
CALIFORNIA

171
00:15:32.126 --> 00:15:33.919
- What the hell was that?
- Are we clear to go in there?

172
00:15:34.086 --> 00:15:35.254
No. sir. They were
using human shields.

173
00:15:35.462 --> 00:15:36.630
We never got the green light.

174
00:15:36.839 --> 00:15:38.799
Department of State.
they're gonna be all over this.

175
00:15:39.716 --> 00:15:41.301
We got a bogey.

176
00:15:41.468 --> 00:15:43.261
Is CIA on the line?

177
00:15:43.470 --> 00:15:45.472
I got them on line.
they wanna know if it's us.

178
00:15:45.638 --> 00:15:47.098
No. that definitely
is not us. sir.

179
00:15:47.265 --> 00:15:49.016
- It wasn't navy.
- Wasn't marines.

180
00:15:49.183 --> 00:15:51.686
I need answers! Can I please
get eyes on target?

181
00:15:52.937 --> 00:15:54.188
Get me colonel Rhodes

182
00:15:54.396 --> 00:15:56.690
from the Weapons development
down here now!

183
00:16:02.028 --> 00:16:03.822
We ran an ID check
and crossed reference

184
00:16:03.989 --> 00:16:05.740
with all known databases.
We have nothing.

185
00:16:05.949 --> 00:16:07.659
Any high-altitude surveillance
in the region?

186
00:16:07.867 --> 00:16:09.577
We've got an AWAC and
a Global Hawk in the area.

187
00:16:09.785 --> 00:16:11.203
So this things just
appeared out of nowhere?

188
00:16:11.412 --> 00:16:12.872
How come it didn't
show up on the Radar?

189
00:16:13.038 --> 00:16:14.748
It's got a minimum Radar
cross-section. sir.

190
00:16:14.957 --> 00:16:16.708
- Is it stealth?
- No. sir. It's tiny.

191
00:16:16.917 --> 00:16:18.961
We think it's an
unmanned aerial vehicle.

192
00:16:19.211 --> 00:16:21.588
Colonel. what are we
dealing with here?

193
00:16:23.506 --> 00:16:25.300
I'm gonna make a call.

194
00:16:29.804 --> 00:16:31.222
- Hello?
- Tony?

195
00:16:31.430 --> 00:16:33.099
- Who is this?
- It's Rhodes.

196
00:16:33.265 --> 00:16:34.391
Sorry. hello?

197
00:16:34.558 --> 00:16:36.352
- I said it's Rhodes.
- Speak up. please.

198
00:16:36.477 --> 00:16:39.563
- What the hell is that noise?
- I'm driving with the top down.

199
00:16:39.771 --> 00:16:41.398
Yeah. well I need
your help right now.

200
00:16:41.606 --> 00:16:43.149
It's funny how
that works. huh?

201
00:16:43.316 --> 00:16:45.318
Yeah. speaking of funny.
we got a weapons depot

202
00:16:45.485 --> 00:16:47.320
that was just blown up
a few cliques from where

203
00:16:47.528 --> 00:16:49.238
you've been held captive.
- Well. that's a hot spot.

204
00:16:49.447 --> 00:16:51.949
Sounds like someone stepped in
and did you job for you.

205
00:16:52.116 --> 00:16:53.742
Why do you sound
out of breath. Tony?

206
00:16:53.951 --> 00:16:55.869
- I was just jogging at the canyon.
- I thought you were driving.

207
00:16:56.036 --> 00:16:57.955
Right. I was driving to the
canyon where I'm gonna jog.

208
00:16:58.163 --> 00:16:59.873
Are you sure you don't have
any tech in that area...

209
00:17:00.082 --> 00:17:01.249
...I should know about?
- Nope.

210
00:17:01.416 --> 00:17:03.001
Bogey spotted!

211
00:17:03.168 --> 00:17:05.170
Okay. good. cause I'm
staring at one right now

212
00:17:05.378 --> 00:17:07.505
and it's about to be
blown to kingdom come

213
00:17:14.762 --> 00:17:17.806
War room. this is Whiplash One.
I've got the bogey in my sight.

214
00:17:18.307 --> 00:17:21.017
- Whiplash One. what is it?
- I've got no idea.

215
00:17:21.101 --> 00:17:23.103
- You have radio contact?
- Non responsive. sir.

216
00:17:23.311 --> 00:17:25.021
Then you are clear to engage.

217
00:17:31.944 --> 00:17:34.488
Bogey just went supersonic.
I got a lock!

218
00:17:38.909 --> 00:17:40.827
Incoming missile.
- Flairs!

219
00:17:43.496 --> 00:17:45.748
Wait a second!
Bogey deployed flairs.

220
00:17:59.636 --> 00:18:01.012
Deploy flaps!

221
00:18:02.305 --> 00:18:04.599
Holly... this thing just
drove off the Radar. sir!

222
00:18:04.766 --> 00:18:06.517
Satellite image has been lost.

223
00:18:06.726 --> 00:18:08.978
- No way that's the U.A.V.
- What is it?

224
00:18:09.187 --> 00:18:10.938
I can't see anything.

225
00:18:11.147 --> 00:18:13.524
Whatever it was.
it just bought the farm.

226
00:18:13.941 --> 00:18:15.901
I think bogey has
been handled. sir.

227
00:18:25.410 --> 00:18:27.412
- Hello? - Hi. Rhodey. it's me.
- It's who?

228
00:18:27.620 --> 00:18:30.373
I'm sorry. it IS me. You asked
what that was. and it was me.

229
00:18:30.540 --> 00:18:33.167
No. see.. this isn't a game.
You do not send civilian equipment

230
00:18:33.375 --> 00:18:35.669
into my active war zone.
You understand that?

231
00:18:35.878 --> 00:18:39.172
It's not a piece of equipment.
I am in it. It's a suit. It's me!

232
00:18:39.506 --> 00:18:41.424
Rhodey. you got anything for me?

233
00:18:43.218 --> 00:18:46.304
Mark your position and
return to base. - Roger that.

234
00:18:48.431 --> 00:18:51.392
On your belly!
It looks like a... man!

235
00:18:51.600 --> 00:18:54.103
Shake him off!
Move. move!

236
00:19:01.818 --> 00:19:03.737
I'm hit!
I'm hit!

237
00:19:09.367 --> 00:19:11.077
Eject! Eject!

238
00:19:17.416 --> 00:19:19.167
Whiplash One down.

239
00:19:19.334 --> 00:19:22.629
- Whiplash 2. do you see a chute?
- Negative! No chute! No chute!

240
00:19:28.301 --> 00:19:30.261
My chute's jammed!

241
00:19:34.765 --> 00:19:36.975
Sir. I've got a visual
on a bogey.

242
00:19:37.226 --> 00:19:40.562
Whiplash 2. reengage. If you
get a clear shot. you take it!

243
00:19:41.813 --> 00:19:44.649
Major. we don't even know what we're
shooting at. Call off the Raptors.

244
00:19:44.899 --> 00:19:47.735
That thing just took out an F-22
inside the legal no-fly zone.

245
00:19:47.860 --> 00:19:49.779
Whiplash 2. if you have
a clear shot. take it.

246
00:19:49.987 --> 00:19:52.365
They've been reengaged.
Execute evasive maneuver.

247
00:19:52.573 --> 00:19:53.699
Keep going!

248
00:20:00.747 --> 00:20:03.166
Got a chute!
Got a chute!

249
00:20:09.922 --> 00:20:12.800
- Tony. are you still there?
- Hey. thanks.

250
00:20:12.967 --> 00:20:15.678
Oh my God. you crazy
son of a bitch!

251
00:20:15.886 --> 00:20:18.138
You owe me a plane.
you know that. right?

252
00:20:19.056 --> 00:20:21.558
Yeah. well. technically
he hit me. so...

253
00:20:21.766 --> 00:20:24.394
Now are you gonna come by and
see what I'm working on? - No. no.

254
00:20:24.561 --> 00:20:26.104
The less I know the better.

255
00:20:26.312 --> 00:20:28.231
Now what am I supposed
to tell to the press?

256
00:20:28.398 --> 00:20:30.274
Training exercise.
Isn't that the usual BS?

257
00:20:30.483 --> 00:20:32.193
It's not that simple.

258
00:20:32.610 --> 00:20:34.486
An unfortunate
training exercise

259
00:20:34.695 --> 00:20:37.406
involving an F-22 Raptor
occurred yesterday.

260
00:20:37.614 --> 00:20:40.534
I'm pleased to report that
the pilot was not injured.

261
00:20:41.118 --> 00:20:44.788
As for the unexpected turn of
events on the ground in Gulmira.

262
00:20:44.996 --> 00:20:48.374
it is still unclear who
or what intervened.

263
00:20:48.541 --> 00:20:52.211
but I can assure you that the U.S.
government was not involved.

264
00:20:57.174 --> 00:20:59.760
Oh. it isn't that bad. sir.

265
00:21:00.010 --> 00:21:02.971
Sir. the more you struggle.
the more this is going to hurt.

266
00:21:03.138 --> 00:21:05.056
Be gentle.
this is my first time.

267
00:21:05.598 --> 00:21:07.475
I designed this to come off.

268
00:21:11.771 --> 00:21:13.731
Please try not to move.

269
00:21:14.773 --> 00:21:16.775
What's going on here?

270
00:21:20.987 --> 00:21:24.324
Let's face it. this is not the worst
thing you've caught me doing.

271
00:21:25.575 --> 00:21:27.744
Are those bullet holes?

272
00:21:53.809 --> 00:21:55.394
Welcome.

273
00:21:58.188 --> 00:22:00.607
Compliments of Tony Stark.

274
00:22:00.982 --> 00:22:04.402
If you killed him when you were
supposed to. you'd still have a face.

275
00:22:04.569 --> 00:22:06.738
You paid us trinkets
to kill a prince.

276
00:22:06.946 --> 00:22:08.906
Show me the weapon.

277
00:22:09.699 --> 00:22:12.952
Come. Leave your
guards outside.

278
00:22:29.008 --> 00:22:31.886
His escape bore
unexpected fruit.

279
00:22:34.013 --> 00:22:36.181
So this is how he did it.

280
00:22:36.598 --> 00:22:40.644
This is only a first crude effort.
Stark has perfected his design.

281
00:22:41.436 --> 00:22:44.481
He has made a
masterpiece of death.

282
00:22:44.647 --> 00:22:47.984
A man with a dozen of these
can rule all of Asia.

283
00:22:49.110 --> 00:22:52.363
And you dream of Stark's throne.

284
00:22:52.988 --> 00:22:55.407
We have a common enemy.

285
00:22:59.453 --> 00:23:01.830
We are still in business.

286
00:23:03.665 --> 00:23:05.834
I will give you these designs...

287
00:23:07.251 --> 00:23:08.878
...as a gift.

288
00:23:09.712 --> 00:23:11.672
And in return...

289
00:23:12.798 --> 00:23:17.344
...I hope you repay me
with a gift of iron soldiers.

290
00:23:28.229 --> 00:23:31.148
This is the only gift
you will receive.

291
00:23:33.984 --> 00:23:35.486
Technology.

292
00:23:37.029 --> 00:23:40.824
That's always been your Achilles
heel in this part of the world.

293
00:23:41.700 --> 00:23:45.036
Don't worry. It will only
last for 15 minutes.

294
00:23:45.662 --> 00:23:48.623
That's the least
of your problems.

295
00:23:53.085 --> 00:23:55.838
Bring the armour
and the rest of it.

296
00:23:57.172 --> 00:23:59.466
Alright. lets finish up here.

297
00:24:02.886 --> 00:24:05.555
Set up Sector 16
underneath the Arc reactor.

298
00:24:05.722 --> 00:24:09.225
And I want this dead and masked.
Recruit our top engineers.

299
00:24:09.392 --> 00:24:11.352
I want a prototype right away.

300
00:24:19.860 --> 00:24:21.236
Are you busy?

301
00:24:21.903 --> 00:24:25.240
I need you to go to my office
and hack into the mainframe.

302
00:24:25.448 --> 00:24:28.368
You're gonna retrieve all
the recent shipping manifests.

303
00:24:28.534 --> 00:24:30.995
This is a lock chip.
this will get you in.

304
00:24:31.203 --> 00:24:33.539
It's probably under
Executive Files. if not...

305
00:24:33.664 --> 00:24:36.000
they put it on a ghost drive.
in which case you need to look

306
00:24:36.208 --> 00:24:37.835
for the lowest
numeric heading.

307
00:24:38.001 --> 00:24:40.212
And what do you plan to do
with this information

308
00:24:40.420 --> 00:24:41.755
if I bring it back here?
- Same drill.

309
00:24:41.922 --> 00:24:44.049
They've been dealing under
the table. I'm gonna stop them.

310
00:24:44.174 --> 00:24:47.051
I'm gonna find my weapons
and destroy them.

311
00:24:47.468 --> 00:24:49.011
Tony...

312
00:24:50.638 --> 00:24:53.349
you know that I would
help you with anything.

313
00:24:53.516 --> 00:24:56.477
but I can not help you if you're
gonna start all of this again.

314
00:24:56.685 --> 00:24:59.896
There is nothing except this.
There's no art openings.

315
00:25:00.105 --> 00:25:03.358
there's no benefit.
there's nothing to sign.

316
00:25:04.234 --> 00:25:07.612
There's the next mission.
and nothing else.

317
00:25:08.738 --> 00:25:10.698
Is that so?

318
00:25:11.866 --> 00:25:13.826
Well. then I quit.

319
00:25:15.994 --> 00:25:17.871
You stood by my side
all these years

320
00:25:18.080 --> 00:25:20.457
while I reaped the
benefits of destruction.

321
00:25:20.791 --> 00:25:22.709
And now that I'm trying
to protect the people

322
00:25:22.876 --> 00:25:24.627
that I've put in harm's way.
your going to walk out?

323
00:25:24.794 --> 00:25:28.631
You're gonna kill yourself. Tony.
I'm not gonna be a part of it.

324
00:25:29.132 --> 00:25:33.177
I shouldn't be alive...
unless it was for a reason.

325
00:25:35.012 --> 00:25:36.972
I'm not crazy. Pepper.

326
00:25:37.181 --> 00:25:40.308
I just finally know
what I have to do.

327
00:25:44.270 --> 00:25:47.649
And I know in my heart
that it's right.

328
00:26:02.204 --> 00:26:04.539
You're all I have
too. you know.

329
00:27:11.142 --> 00:27:13.060
Sector 16?

330
00:27:14.186 --> 00:27:16.105
What are you up to. Obadiah?

331
00:27:28.157 --> 00:27:30.993
You did not tell us that
the target you paid us to kill

332
00:27:31.202 --> 00:27:33.412
was the great Tony Stark.
As you can see.

333
00:27:33.621 --> 00:27:36.457
Obadiah Stane. your deception
and lies will cost you dearly.

334
00:27:36.623 --> 00:27:39.459
The price to kill Tony Stark
has just gone up.

335
00:27:43.338 --> 00:27:47.008
So... what are we
gonna do about this?

336
00:27:58.560 --> 00:28:02.022
I know what you're
going through. Pepper.

337
00:28:09.529 --> 00:28:12.907
Ah. Tony. He always gets
the good stuff. doesn't he?

338
00:28:33.509 --> 00:28:35.594
I was so happy...

339
00:28:36.845 --> 00:28:40.974
when he came home. It was like
we got him back from the dead.

340
00:28:43.518 --> 00:28:45.562
And now I realise...

341
00:28:47.772 --> 00:28:51.484
...well. Tony never really
did come home. did he?

342
00:28:52.234 --> 00:28:55.195
He left a part of himself
in that cave.

343
00:28:57.614 --> 00:28:59.574
Breaks my heart.

344
00:29:01.118 --> 00:29:02.369
Well...

345
00:29:03.453 --> 00:29:05.622
He is a complicated person.

346
00:29:07.749 --> 00:29:11.419
He's been through a lot.
I think he'll be alright.

347
00:29:17.299 --> 00:29:20.177
You are a very rare woman.

348
00:29:22.178 --> 00:29:24.681
Tony doesn't know
how lucky he is.

349
00:29:26.724 --> 00:29:28.851
Thank you. Thanks.

350
00:29:30.853 --> 00:29:32.772
I gotta get back there.

351
00:29:37.818 --> 00:29:40.112
Is that today's paper?

352
00:29:41.321 --> 00:29:42.530
Yes.

353
00:29:43.114 --> 00:29:45.825
- Do you mind?
- Not at all.

354
00:29:46.034 --> 00:29:48.244
- Puzzle.
- Of course.

355
00:29:51.455 --> 00:29:53.249
Take care.

356
00:30:15.644 --> 00:30:17.437
Ms. Potts?
We had an appointment.

357
00:30:17.521 --> 00:30:19.398
Did you forget about
our appointment?

358
00:30:19.564 --> 00:30:22.192
Nope. Right now.
come with me.

359
00:30:24.152 --> 00:30:27.071
I'll give you the meeting
of your life. Your office.

360
00:30:28.072 --> 00:30:30.533
We've been working our best.

361
00:30:31.033 --> 00:30:33.953
Absolutely. we're... I'm gonna
have to call you back.

362
00:30:34.578 --> 00:30:37.623
Mr. Stane? Sir. we've explored
what you've asked us

363
00:30:37.831 --> 00:30:40.542
and it seems as though there's
a little hiccup. actually...

364
00:30:40.751 --> 00:30:42.961
- A hiccup?
- Yes. to power the suit...

365
00:30:43.128 --> 00:30:45.463
sir. the technology actually
doesn't exist. So it's...

366
00:30:45.713 --> 00:30:47.632
Wait. wait. the technology?

367
00:30:48.091 --> 00:30:51.177
William. here is
the technology.

368
00:30:51.635 --> 00:30:54.013
I've asked you to simply
make it smaller.

369
00:30:54.221 --> 00:30:56.473
Okay. sir. that's what
we're trying to do.

370
00:30:56.682 --> 00:30:58.600
but honestly.
it's impossible.

371
00:30:58.767 --> 00:31:01.937
Tony Stark was able
to build this in a cave!

372
00:31:02.437 --> 00:31:04.731
With a box of scraps!

373
00:31:06.274 --> 00:31:09.610
I'm sorry.
I'm not Tony Stark.

374
00:31:24.666 --> 00:31:26.000
Tony?

375
00:31:28.294 --> 00:31:30.046
Tony. are you there?

376
00:31:33.132 --> 00:31:34.425
Breathe.

377
00:31:35.301 --> 00:31:37.636
Easy. easy...

378
00:31:40.055 --> 00:31:42.557
You remember this one. right?

379
00:31:43.600 --> 00:31:46.019
It's a shame the government
didn't approve.

380
00:31:46.227 --> 00:31:49.939
There are so many applications
regarding short-term paralysis.

381
00:31:51.774 --> 00:31:53.359
Ah. Tony.

382
00:31:55.819 --> 00:31:59.656
When I ordered
the hit on you.

383
00:32:02.325 --> 00:32:04.869
I was worried that I was...

384
00:32:07.664 --> 00:32:10.291
...killing the golden goose.

385
00:32:11.125 --> 00:32:13.085
But. you see...

386
00:32:13.836 --> 00:32:17.714
it was just fate
that you survived it.

387
00:32:23.011 --> 00:32:26.681
leaving one last
golden egg to give.

388
00:32:30.810 --> 00:32:34.146
You really think that just
because you have an idea.

389
00:32:34.355 --> 00:32:36.273
it belongs to you?

390
00:32:39.443 --> 00:32:43.530
Your father. he helped to
give us the atomic bomb.

391
00:32:43.697 --> 00:32:46.574
Now what kind of world
would it be today

392
00:32:46.783 --> 00:32:48.701
if he was as selfish as you?

393
00:32:58.126 --> 00:33:00.128
Oh. it's beautiful.

394
00:33:02.380 --> 00:33:03.923
Ah. Tony...

395
00:33:05.258 --> 00:33:07.677
This is your Ninth Symphony.

396
00:33:08.970 --> 00:33:11.722
What a masterpiece!
Look at that.

397
00:33:12.681 --> 00:33:14.808
This is your legacy.

398
00:33:16.935 --> 00:33:19.646
The generation of weapons...

399
00:33:20.272 --> 00:33:22.607
...with this at its heart.

400
00:33:24.818 --> 00:33:28.488
The weapons that will help
stir the world back on course.

401
00:33:28.696 --> 00:33:31.365
With the balance of power
in our hands.

402
00:33:32.324 --> 00:33:34.285
In the right hands.

403
00:33:36.954 --> 00:33:41.249
I wish you could see
my prototype.

404
00:33:42.709 --> 00:33:47.672
It's not as... not as
conservative as yours.

405
00:33:50.007 --> 00:33:52.676
Too bad you had to
involve Pepper in this.

406
00:33:53.219 --> 00:33:55.679
I would've preferred
that she lived.

407
00:34:08.107 --> 00:34:10.109
What do you mean he paid
to have Tony killed?

408
00:34:10.318 --> 00:34:12.069
Pepper. slow down.

409
00:34:12.278 --> 00:34:15.239
Why would Obadiah...
okay. where is Tony now?

410
00:34:15.406 --> 00:34:17.533
I don't know. he's not
answering his phone.

411
00:34:17.741 --> 00:34:19.785
Please go there and make
sure everything's okay.

412
00:34:19.951 --> 00:34:22.329
Thank you. Rhodey.
I know a shortcut.

413
00:35:25.553 --> 00:35:27.096
Good boy.

414
00:36:05.006 --> 00:36:06.132
Tony?

415
00:36:08.593 --> 00:36:10.094
Tony?

416
00:36:11.387 --> 00:36:12.680
Tony?

417
00:36:18.143 --> 00:36:19.353
Tony!

418
00:36:22.647 --> 00:36:24.983
- Are you okay?
- Where is Pepper?

419
00:36:25.692 --> 00:36:29.237
She's fine. She's with five agents
that are about to arrest Obadiah.

420
00:36:29.820 --> 00:36:31.739
That's not gonna be enough.

421
00:36:54.718 --> 00:36:56.470
Section 16.

422
00:36:57.387 --> 00:36:59.014
Section 16...

423
00:36:59.639 --> 00:37:01.099
There it is.

424
00:37:09.106 --> 00:37:11.442
My key's not working.
it's not opening the door.

425
00:37:11.692 --> 00:37:14.028
Wow. what is that? It's like
a little device. like a thing

426
00:37:14.236 --> 00:37:17.364
that's gonna pick the lock?
-You may wanna take few steps back.

427
00:37:35.881 --> 00:37:39.009
That's the coolest thing I've
ever seen. - Not bad. huh?

428
00:37:40.302 --> 00:37:41.845
Let's do it.

429
00:37:47.558 --> 00:37:49.769
You need me to do
anything else?

430
00:37:50.186 --> 00:37:52.063
Keep the skies clear.

431
00:37:56.692 --> 00:37:58.110
Damn!

432
00:38:05.575 --> 00:38:07.493
Next time. baby.

433
00:38:36.311 --> 00:38:38.063
Looks like you were right.

434
00:38:38.397 --> 00:38:39.981
He was building a suit.

435
00:38:40.190 --> 00:38:42.067
I thought it'll be bigger.

436
00:39:25.064 --> 00:39:26.441
Take him out!

437
00:39:36.325 --> 00:39:38.702
How do you think the Mark One
chest piece is gonna hold up?

438
00:39:38.869 --> 00:39:40.662
48% power and falling. sir.

439
00:39:40.871 --> 00:39:43.707
That chest piece was never
designed for sustained flight.

440
00:39:43.915 --> 00:39:45.416
Keep me posted.

441
00:39:46.668 --> 00:39:48.044
- Pepper.
- Tony?

442
00:39:48.252 --> 00:39:50.087
- Tony. are you okay?
- I'm fine.

443
00:39:50.296 --> 00:39:52.465
- Obadiah. he's gone insane.
- I know. Listen!

444
00:39:52.673 --> 00:39:54.758
- You better get outta there!
- He built the suit.

445
00:39:54.967 --> 00:39:56.343
Get outta there. right now!

446
00:40:06.978 --> 00:40:09.272
Where do you think
you're going?

447
00:40:14.652 --> 00:40:17.196
Your services are
no longer required.

448
00:40:17.905 --> 00:40:19.114
Stane!

449
00:40:43.345 --> 00:40:45.763
- I love this suit!
- Put them down.

450
00:40:45.972 --> 00:40:48.182
Collateral damage. Tony.

451
00:40:49.433 --> 00:40:51.560
Defer the power
to chest piece.

452
00:41:00.068 --> 00:41:02.112
Power reduced to 19%.

453
00:41:09.202 --> 00:41:10.453
Lady!

454
00:41:35.934 --> 00:41:38.979
For thirty years.
I've been holding you up.

455
00:41:42.649 --> 00:41:45.401
I built this company
from nothing!

456
00:41:47.070 --> 00:41:49.864
And nothing is gonna
stand in my way.

457
00:41:55.577 --> 00:41:57.996
And least of all. you.

458
00:42:07.171 --> 00:42:09.924
Impressive!
You upgraded your armour.

459
00:42:10.132 --> 00:42:13.010
I've made some
upgrades of my own.

460
00:42:20.934 --> 00:42:22.852
Sir. it appears that
his suit can fly.

461
00:42:23.061 --> 00:42:25.021
Duly noted. Take me
to the maximum altitude.

462
00:42:25.188 --> 00:42:27.523
With only 15% power. the odds
of reaching that altitude...

463
00:42:27.732 --> 00:42:29.609
I know the math! Do it!

464
00:42:37.032 --> 00:42:39.618
Sir. you're not gonna believe this.
That thing is back.

465
00:42:39.785 --> 00:42:42.078
Get me major Allen.
Scramble the jets!

466
00:42:44.456 --> 00:42:47.583
Not necessary. people.
just the training exercise.

467
00:42:56.592 --> 00:42:58.760
- 13% power. sir.
- Climb!

468
00:43:02.264 --> 00:43:04.349
-11%.
- Keep going!

469
00:43:10.855 --> 00:43:13.941
- 7% power. - Just leave it on
the screen. stop telling me.

470
00:43:23.616 --> 00:43:25.118
You had a great idea. Tony.

471
00:43:25.326 --> 00:43:27.995
but my suit is more
advanced in every way!

472
00:43:28.204 --> 00:43:30.456
How'd you solve
the icing problem?

473
00:43:30.581 --> 00:43:32.124
Icing problem?

474
00:43:34.043 --> 00:43:35.878
Might want to look into it.

475
00:43:47.472 --> 00:43:48.806
2%.

476
00:43:50.808 --> 00:43:53.727
We are now running on
emergency backup power.

477
00:44:04.654 --> 00:44:05.905
- Potts!
- Tony!

478
00:44:06.114 --> 00:44:08.074
Oh my God. are you okay?

479
00:44:08.241 --> 00:44:11.160
I'm almost dead of power.
I gotta get out of this thing.

480
00:44:11.327 --> 00:44:13.954
I'll be right there.
- Nice try.

481
00:44:25.757 --> 00:44:27.467
Weapons status?

482
00:44:27.675 --> 00:44:29.802
Repulsors are off line.

483
00:44:33.681 --> 00:44:35.015
Flairs!

484
00:44:43.356 --> 00:44:45.567
Very clever. Tony.

485
00:44:50.404 --> 00:44:52.198
- Potts.
- Tony!

486
00:44:52.406 --> 00:44:54.908
This isn't working. we're gonna
have to overload the reactor

487
00:44:55.117 --> 00:44:57.661
