She'd be a wreck.

546
00:49:51.263 --> 00:49:53.557
She'd always be worrying
that I was gonna die.

547
00:49:53.766 --> 00:49:56.101
and yet proud of a man
I become. She'd be...

548
00:49:56.268 --> 00:49:59.312
wildly conflicted. which
would only make her more...

549
00:50:00.230 --> 00:50:03.066
crazy about me. Tell me you
never think about that night?

550
00:50:03.191 --> 00:50:05.151
- What night?
- You know.

551
00:50:07.570 --> 00:50:11.073
Are you talking about...
the night that we danced.

552
00:50:11.657 --> 00:50:14.118
and went up to the roof...

553
00:50:14.702 --> 00:50:16.036
and then...

554
00:50:16.995 --> 00:50:20.874
you went downstairs
to get me a drink. and you...

555
00:50:21.666 --> 00:50:23.918
left me there by myself?

556
00:50:24.210 --> 00:50:26.671
Is that the night
you're talking about?

557
00:50:28.923 --> 00:50:30.633
I thought so.

558
00:50:32.510 --> 00:50:36.055
- Will that be all. Mr. Stark?
- Yes. that'd be all. Ms. Potts.

559
00:50:36.263 --> 00:50:39.224
And now Mr. Stark has
prepared a statement.

560
00:50:39.558 --> 00:50:42.602
He will not be taking
any questions. thank you.

561
00:50:45.688 --> 00:50:48.608
It's been a while since
I was in front of you.

562
00:50:48.816 --> 00:50:51.485
I figure I'll stick
to the cards this time.

563
00:50:53.028 --> 00:50:55.322
There's been speculation that
I was involved in the events

564
00:50:55.531 --> 00:50:57.449
that occurred on a freeway
and the rooftop...

565
00:50:57.658 --> 00:51:00.619
I'm sorry Mr. Stark. but do you
honestly expect us to believe that

